 Autoren der Weltliteratur sowie internationale/interkulturelle Vergleiche bilden die weiteren Themenbereiche der insgesamt 50 enthaltenen Artikel.  aThe Handbook presents an overview of political speech, including its history, manifestations, traditional genres, text forms, characteristic tools, medial forms, and typical functions. In addition, the 50 articles offer analyses of rhetoric based on major authors in world literature as well as international and intercultural comparison.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aRhetoricxPolitical aspects. 4aPolitische Kommunikation. 4aPolitische Rede. 4aPolitische Rhetorik. 4aTropus. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Rhetoric.2bisacsh  aPolitical Communication.  aPolitical Speech.  aRhetoric in Politics.  aTrope.1 aAdamski, Irina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAzuma, Shoji, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeise, Arnd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBerger, Grazia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBernard, Wolfgang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBernsmeier, Helmut, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlank, Thomas G. M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBock, Bettina M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoyken, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurggraf, Stefan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurkhardt, Armin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurkhardt, Armin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCherednyk, Maryna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id